rComments: Her multiple choice is horrible. Very hard to do well in her course. I hated her teaching style.

Very nice and fair prof. This was a very interesting course and she taught it very well. The assignment was very fair, not too much work. The midterm/final are a bit subjective, but overall fair. Would recommend this prof.

Sarah Fraser is the most well rounded professors in the faculty of Health Sciences. She is always available to answer questions in and outside of class. Professor Fraser is also one of the most caring professors I have encountered at the university. If you do the readings and watch the lectures you can do extremely well in this class!
Everything is in her lectures and readings she provides from class. Super interesting for the most part, sometimes dry but she tries her best to make it somewhat worth listening to.

Dr Fraser makes the subject really interesting, if u show up to class, will be easier to study for the exams bc she gives examples. Lots of assigned readings but they aren't terrible. Project has to be done in groups, strict w rubric so be careful but she gives amazing and helpful feedback. Lot of choice MCQs so you have to study well. Good prof!!
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Extremely inaccessible out of class. Does not answer emails and doesnt care. Strict and unclear grading criteria. Only take this class if youre ready for your GPA to drop
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Group projects', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Important to attend her lectures because her slides are hard to understand without context. Paper is marked tough. Midterm and final are based off her slides and the readings (make sure to do them!) and attend the review sessions. They're helpful. Not an impossible class but definitely not easy to get an A/A+

I LOVED her tech and health class. Alot of students in the past havent said many good things about her but with her new teaching style this semester, she has made the class super fair. Although the assignment was graded tough, her exams are super easy. This prof has inspired me to do a career in tech and health, i absolutely love her!!

one of the nicest profs on campus. i know u might be thrown off by alot of the negative reviews but she changed her class format and lecture style. She made her class super easy and fair. Exams are copy and paste from lectures. Make sure to do the reading questions, the same questions come up in the exams. go to the exam review session. easy A

She's an interesting lecturer and definitely treated the course properly, covering a wide variety of subjects. However, her evaluations are incredibly difficult to do better than 80% on, despite pretty easy content. She words questions so poorly I almost wonder if she does it on purpose to keep grades low. Avoid if aiming for an A/A+...

Her exams are not that hard, but some of the MCQ are really subjective so it makes it impossible to get a high grade. Dont waste your time with the readings, her PPTs have all the info that you need and readings are just there for clarification. The paper should boost your mark if you follow every little criteria in the rubric. Interesting course.

The class itself is very interesting! I was just not a fan of Dr Fraser and her monotonous voice. Her midterms are mostly based on readings we had to do and also learning random statistics by heart. Multiple choice questions with choices like: A and B, B and C.... which makes her midterms 10x harder!

Interesting class. No textbook, do the readings and assigned questions. Her classes are straightforward and pretty boring (she's a bit monotonous) but definitely go for the guest lecturers. Midterm and group project were easy. The final was destructive. I went in with the high end of an A and I'm not even sure I'll finish the course with a B+...

the course is really interesting and straight forward. the group project is tricky. prof Sarah know her stuff and is always available for questions .. even though there is a  lot of reading the prof usually post questions for them so focus on that and even if you do that some of the questions on the midterm and final will surprise you lol

I get the feeling she doesn't enjoy teaching. Lack of enthusiasm. If you ask her a question on material not covered in the slides she's lost. No textbook and group project. Most of the test questions are based on the readings. Reads directly off the slides and anything she adds in class is not testable material. There's no point in attending class.
Do all the readings they are a huge part of the final and midterm

I really liked Dr Fraser! Her lectures were interesting and she was always very enthusiastic, and nice! No textbook, just online readings (but there were a lot). DEFINITELY read the readings. A lot of people got caught off guard because they didn't study them enough. She really emphasizes them. Good class, definitely worth taking.

Overall average professor, however, was very unclear about the class assignment. Told students to follow the rubric but it was poorly designed so it did not offer much guidance. Relatively interesting material. No textbook, lots of posted articles to read.

She is a good prof in the sense she is eager to help you and wants you to succeed. Her midterm and final I found were extremely easy. When it comes to the group project, she is pretty tough; the grades were between 50 and 80. If you study really hard for the exams you can pull of a good grade. The lectures I found useless if you go to class.

She's a nice person. The lectures were pretty boring, but she usually picked out interesting videos to show the class. Midterm was confusing and imprecise & it was way too easy to lose points as each error resulted in a 1% drop in your final grade. Group project is NOT a grade booster, work hard/choose your partners wisely. Final was easy.

She's definitely new to teaching. Lectures were boring, slides were simple but confusing at times. No real need to go to class. Midterm and final were MCQ (1Q  1%). The group project was vague, but it wasn't very difficult. She's nice, but isn't good at teaching concepts. Exam grades were high, project was a little lower.
